The '''spot-tailed sparrowhawk''' or '''spot-tailed goshawk''' ('''''Tachyspiza trinotata''''') is a species of [[bird of prey]] in the family, [[Accipitridae]]. It was formerly placed in the [[genus]] ''[[Accipiter]]''. It is [[Endemism|endemic]] to [[Sulawesi]] in [[Indonesia]]. Its natural [[habitat]]s are [[subtropical or tropical moist lowland forest]] and subtropical or tropical [[mangrove forest]].

== Description ==
It has a length of 26-30 cm and a wingspan of 45-51 cm.<ref>{{Cite book |last=Ferguson-Lees |first=James |title=Raptors of the World |date=2005 |publisher=Bloomsbury Publishing Plc |others=David A. Christie |isbn=978-0-7136-6957-2 |series=Helm Field Guides |location=London}}</ref>

